# âŒ¨ï¸ Linux Typing Practice Program â€“ **KTouch**

## ğŸ“Œ What is KTouch?
**KTouch** is a free, open-source typing tutor for Linux, developed as part of the KDE project.  
It is designed to help users improve typing speed and accuracy through **structured lessons, real-time feedback, and progress tracking**.

KTouch is suitable for:
- Beginners learning keyboard layout
- Users practicing daily typing
- Linux users looking for a lightweight, stable typing trainer

---

## ğŸ–¥ï¸ Supported Environments
- Debian / Ubuntu / Linux Mint
- XFCE, GNOME, KDE, LXQt
- Works well with **fcitx / fcitx5** input methods

---

## âœ¨ Key Features

### âœ… Structured Typing Lessons
- Step-by-step lessons from basic keys to full sentences
- Gradual difficulty increase
- Focus on proper finger placement

### âœ… Real-Time Feedback
- Typing speed (WPM)
- Accuracy rate
- Error highlighting while typing

### âœ… Progress Tracking
- Lesson completion history
- Speed improvement over time
- Accuracy statistics

### âœ… Multi-Language Support
- English layouts included by default
- Custom layouts can be added
- Works with Korean input (Hangul) when system IME is configured correctly

### âœ… Clean GUI
- Simple, distraction-free interface
- No ads, no account required
- Lightweight and responsive

